Package: VaccineValidateR
Type: Package
Title: Vaccine Validator for United States Childhood Immunization Schedules
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2025-11-24
Authors@R: 
    person("Jeremy J.", "Michel", 
           email = "michelj@chop.edu", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Jeremy J Michel <michelj@chop.edu>
License: file LICENSE
Description: VaccineValidateR provides tools to clean, standardize, and validate 
    childhood immunization data according to U.S. ACIP recommendations and 
    Immunize.org guidance. It supports mapping of local immunization codes to 
    CVX, validation of dose timing and series completion, and automated detection 
    of invalid or out-of-sequence doses for routine and catch-up schedules 
    (including COVID-19, Influenza, Tetanus, HIB, PCV, and Polio). The package 
    facilitates reproducible vaccine validation workflows for research and 
    clinical quality improvement.
